analysis: The documents all concern the revocation of previous executive orders that had withdrawn public lands, and the subsequent opening of those lands for homesteading and desert land entry, specifically prioritizing qualified ex-service men for a 91-day period following the official filing of the plat of resurvey. The documents span the administrations of Coolidge, Hoover, and Roosevelt, and reference Public Resolution 85 (or No. 29) which provides preferential treatment to ex-service men.
title: Land Opening for Ex-Service Men Following Resurvey
